I"Ù<p>The Elbow Method is used to determine if the best K and to judge if a K-Means algorithm is good.</p>

<h3 id="how-to-judge-if-a-k-means-algorithm-is-good">How to judge if a K-means algorithm is good?</h3>

<ul>
  <li>First you need a measure: one of the most popular one is named â€œdistortionâ€ or â€œSSEâ€ based on sum of squared errors (SSE), (datapoint - centroid)^2.</li>
  <li>Compare distortion with K. The best K is at the rapid change point, creating elbow shape.</li>
  <li>This method is usually called â€œelbowâ€ method because the shape is like an elbow.</li>
  <li>Question: why larger K, less distortion?</li>
</ul>

